data.name: ANSI_FindTables
data.value: select TABLE_SCHEMA, TABLE_NAME from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES where TABLE_TYPE = 'BASE TABLE' order by TABLE_SCHEMA, TABLE_NAME

data.name: ANSI_FindViews
data.value: select TABLE_SCHEMA, TABLE_NAME from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.VIEWS order by TABLE_SCHEMA, TABLE_NAME

data.name: DefaultConnectionString
data.value: Data Source=%TEMP%\Test.db3

data.name: SQLite_FindColumns
data.value: PRAGMA table_info(@TableName)

data.name: SQLite_FindTables
SQLite_FindViews
ANSI_FindColumns
data.value: select c.COLUMN_NAME as name, c.DATA_TYPE + ISNULL('(' + cast(c.character_maximum_length as varchar) + ')', '') + case when c.DATA_TYPE in ('decimal', 'numeric') then ISNULL('(' + cast(c.NUMERIC_PRECISION as varchar) + ', ' + CAST(c.NUMERIC_SCALE as varchar) + ')', '') else '' end as type, c.IS_NULLABLE, sum(case when tc.CONSTRAINT_TYPE = 'PRIMARY KEY' and kcu.COLUMN_NAME is not null then 1 else 0 end) as PKCount, sum(case when tc.CONSTRAINT_TYPE = 'FOREIGN KEY' and kcu.COLUMN_NAME is not null then 1 else 0 end) as FKCount from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS c left join INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS tc on tc.TABLE_SCHEMA = c.TABLE_SCHEMA and tc.TABLE_NAME = c.TABLE_NAME left join INFORMATION_SCHEMA.KEY_COLUMN_USAGE kcu on tc.TABLE_SCHEMA = kcu.TABLE_SCHEMA and tc.TABLE_NAME = kcu.TABLE_NAME and tc.CONSTRAINT_NAME = kcu.CONSTRAINT_NAME and c.COLUMN_NAME = kcu.COLUMN_NAME where c.TABLE_SCHEMA = @SchemaName and c.TABLE_NAME = @TableName group by c.COLUMN_NAME, c.DATA_TYPE, c.CHARACTER_MAXIMUM_LENGTH, c.NUMERIC_PRECISION, c.NUMERIC_SCALE, c.IS_NULLABLE

data.name: SQLServer_FindDatabases
data.value: select name from sys.databases order by 1

data.name: SQLServer_SetDatabase
data.value:
if exists (select 1 from sys.databases d where d.name = @DatabaseName) begin
use @DatabaseReplaceName
end

data.name: DB2_FindColumns
data.value: select LTRIM(RTRIM(c.COLNAME)) as COLNAME, NULLS, case when TYPENAME = 'DECIMAL' then CONCAT(LTRIM(RTRIM(TYPENAME)), CONCAT(' (',CONCAT(LENGTH, CONCAT(', ', CONCAT(SCALE, ')'))))) when TYPENAME like '%CHAR%' then CONCAT(LTRIM(RTRIM(TYPENAME)), CONCAT(' (',CONCAT(LENGTH, ')'))) else LTRIM(RTRIM(TYPENAME)) end as COLTYPE, case when KEYSEQ is not null then 1 else 0 end as IsPrimaryKey, count(k.COLNAME) as FKCount from syscat.columns c left join syscat.tabconst tc on c.TABSCHEMA = tc.TABSCHEMA and c.TABNAME = tc.TABNAME and tc.TYPE = 'F' left join syscat.keycoluse k on tc.CONSTNAME = k.CONSTNAME and tc.TABSCHEMA = k.TABSCHEMA and tc.TABNAME = k.TABNAME and c.COLNAME = k.COLNAME where c.tabschema = @SchemaName and c.tabname = @TableName group by c.COLNO, c.KEYSEQ, c.COLNAME, c.TYPENAME, c.LENGTH, c.SCALE, c.NULLS order by COLNO

data.name: DB2_FindTables
data.value: select LTRIM(RTRIM(TABSCHEMA)) as SCHEMA, LTRIM(RTRIM(TABNAME)) as NAME from syscat.tables where type = 'T' and ownertype = 'U' and card >= 0 order by tabschema, tabname

data.name: DB2_FindViews
data.value: select LTRIM(RTRIM(VIEWSCHEMA)) as SCHEMA, LTRIM(RTRIM(VIEWNAME)) as NAME from syscat.views where ownertype = 'U' and viewschema not like 'SYS%' order by viewschema, viewname

data.name: Teradata_FindColumns
data.value: help column @DatabaseName.@TableName.*

data.name: Teradata_FindDatabases
data.value: select DatabaseName from DBC.DatabasesX order by 1

data.name: Teradata_FindTables
data.value: select TableName from DBC.TablesX where DatabaseName = ? and TableKind = 'T' order by TableName

data.name: Teradata_FindViews
data.value: select TableName from DBC.TablesX where DatabaseName = ? and TableKind = 'V' order by TableName

data.name: ODBC_SetDatabase
data.value:
if exists (select 1 from sys.databases d where d.name = ?) begin
use @DatabaseReplaceName
end

data.name: SQLite_FindForeignKeys
data.value: pragma foreign_key_list(@TableName)

data.name: Teradata_FindForeignKeys
data.value: select ChildKeyColumn from dbc.all_ri_children where ChildDB = @DatabaseName and ChildTable = @TableName

data.name: ANSI_FindKeys
data.value: select tc.CONSTRAINT_NAME, case when CONSTRAINT_TYPE = 'PRIMARY KEY' then 1 when CONSTRAINT_TYPE = 'FOREIGN KEY' then 2 else 0 end as KeyType from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLE_CONSTRAINTS tc where tc.TABLE_SCHEMA = @SchemaName and tc.TABLE_NAME = @TableName and tc.CONSTRAINT_TYPE in ('PRIMARY KEY', 'FOREIGN KEY') order by KeyType, CONSTRAINT_NAME

data.name: DB2_FindKeys
data.value: select CONSTNAME, case when TYPE = 'P' then 1 when TYPE = 'F' then 2 else 0 end as KeyType from syscat.tabconst tc where tc.type in ('P', 'F') and tc.TABSCHEMA = @SchemaName and tc.TABNAME = @TableName order by KeyType, CONSTNAME

data.name: Teradata_SetDatabase
data.value: set session database @DatabaseName
